author: Johnny Lieu
title: Weird Yellow Tail wine Super Bowl ad embarrasses a nation of Twitter users
text:
The Kangaroo Jack of wine, Yellow Tail, has managed to do something not even Fosters beer or pseudo-Aussie restaurant chain Outback Steakhouse has achieved: Embarrass the hell out of actual Australians. Why? The brand's 30-second Super Bowl Sunday advertisement.
It features some dude in a bright yellow suit, running his mouth about how drinking Yellow Tail wine equals a fun time, hanging with an animated kangaroo DJ and a thinly-veiled dick joke aimed at bikini-clad model, Ellie Gonsalves. It's a mess.
SEE ALSO: Watch Lady Gaga's triumphant Super Bowl halftime show in full
Just watch.
After Australia's Prime Minister was recently yelled at by Trump, the last thing the land Down Under needs is an additional battering from a terrible ad for even more terrible wine.
Twitter gets it.
The Yellowtail Super Bowl ad humiliated my country more than Trump ever could.
— Steve Hind (@stevehind) February 6, 2017
OMFG, that Yellow Tail wine ad.
On behalf of Australia, we apologise.
— Peter Phelps MLC (@PeterPhelpsMLC) February 6, 2017
Who the hell is responsible for that horrid #yellowtail advertisement? You're on thin ice America. Thin ice. pic.twitter.com/KlwBVExy0Y
— Kelly (@divabooknerd) February 6, 2017
So Yellowtail is going to shove an obnoxious Aussie in a silly suit into the #SuperBowl at the worst possible time. https://t.co/uhOkAoJMn6
— Matt Bevan (@MatthewBevan) February 5, 2017
What hurt USA / Aussie relations more, Trump or that Yellowtail ad? Yikes.
— Bob Moczydlowsky (@bobmoz) February 6, 2017
a) nobody drinks yellowtail
b) there are no kangaroos at parties
c) we don't say 'pet' we say 'pat'
d) what the fuck
— kimberly (@ohmyemilybett) February 6, 2017
Yellow Tail: Wine for all us millenials #Süperböwl #SB51 pic.twitter.com/gpNQ0prbIO
— Jon Baker (@JonBaker) February 6, 2017
Ew yellow tail don't drink that shit it's cat piss
— Stella ✨ (@jakobschychrun) February 6, 2017
It's been a rough week for Australia but surely that Yellow Tail #SuperBowl Ad with the DJing kangaroo was the low point.
— Josephine Tovey (@Jo_Tovey) February 6, 2017
Unsurprisingly, the commercial wasn't created by Australians. It's the product of U.S. advertising agency Burns Group, according to AdNews .
Dutch-Norwegian Harald Zwart — whose credits include films such as Agent Cody Banks and the 2010 reboot of The Karate Kid — directed the commercial.
Fair enough if the ad gets more Americans drinking Australian wine, but let it be known: Most Aussies consider themselves better than that p*ss.
